<div local-class='blurb'>
  <div local-class='intro'>

		<p>
    This is a fork of <a href="https://crates.io">crates.io</a> for
    the purpose of experimenting with namespaces as described in
    <a href="https://github.com/Manishearth/namespacing-rfc/blob/main/0000-packages-as-optional-namespaces.md">this RFC</a>.
		</p>
		<p><strong>The contents of this registry may be deleted at any time as part of the experiment. DO NOT RELY ON THE CONTENTS OF THIS REGISTRY.</strong></p>

		<p>
    The source code for this instance of crates.io is available on <a href="https://github.com/integer32llc/crates.io/tree/subcrates">Github</a>.
		</p>

  </div>

  <div local-class='stats'>
    <StatsValue
      @label="Downloads"
      @value={{if this.hasData (format-num this.model.num_downloads) "---,---,---"}}
      @icon="file-archive"
      local-class="downloads"
      data-test-total-downloads
    />
    <StatsValue
      @label="Crates in stock"
      @value={{if this.hasData (format-num this.model.num_crates) "---,---"}}
      @icon="box"
      local-class="crates"
      data-test-total-crates
    />
  </div>
</div>

<div>
<h2>Setup</h2>
<p>
    To use this registry to publish and use crates with namespaces, you need to install Caeg's fork of Cargo. See
    <a href="https://github.com/caeg-industries/cargo">https://github.com/caeg-industries/cargo</a> for installation
    instructions.
</p>

<p>Once you have the fork of Cargo set up, you can use this registry to
test out the namespacing functionality. The URL of the index for this
fork is <a href="https://github.com/integer32llc/crates.io-namespace-fork-index.git">
https://github.com/integer32llc/crates.io-namespace-fork-index.git</a></p>

<p>Create a <code>.cargo/config.toml</code> file in your project with the following contents to tell Cargo about the registry and name it <code>cratespaces</code> (or whatever you'd like):</p>
<pre><code>[registries]
cratespaces = { index = "https://github.com/integer32llc/crates.io-namespace-fork-index.git" }
</code></pre>

<p>Sign in to this instance with your GitHub account, create a new token, and log in with:</p>
<pre><code>$ cargo login --registry cratespaces [token value]</code></pre>

<p>To publish packages to this fork, add <code>--registry cratespaces</code> to your publish commands.</p>
<pre><code>cargo +subcrate publish \
    --registry cratespaces</code></pre>

<p>To depend on a package that has already been published to this fork, add the <code>registry</code> setting to your dependencies in Cargo.toml. For example:</p>
<pre><code>[package]
name = "my-package"

[dependencies]
"foo/bar" = { version = "0.1.0", registry = "cratespaces" }
</code></pre>

<p>For more information, the full docs on how to use an alternative
registry is available in <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/reference/registries.html#using-an-alternate-registry">
Cargo's docs</a>.</p>
</div>

{{#if this.dataTask.lastComplete.error}}
